            "worstRating": "1"
          },
          "reviewBody": "Must read review:\nWe were very impressed with the school and their ideologies of Aurobindo brought by Priyanka mam. But i dont think its been implemented at the ground level. I went for my child's(2.5yrs) admission. He had been called for 2 hours classroom session for 2 days for getting judged. As it was a classroom session and parent should also accompany him. He being an active child and parent's presence was throwing tantrums and was not been selected. Even we as a parent didnt got a chance to explain ourselves.\n\n1. How can u judge 2 years child and that too in presence of all children and toys? When a kid will see toy, obviously a normal kid will play with it. They are expecting your child to follow didi's instructions and follow the discipline the other students are following on the assessment day itself.\n2. You should have thoroughly interviewed parent's rather child whether they will cope up with your values.\n3. Also be ready to take leaves for interaction.\n4. After calling them, they gave me reason: less attention and less social skills.\n\nTo all the parents, Every kid is different and love to your kids from my side. All the best.",
          "publisher": {
            "@type": "Organization",
            "name": "Yellow Slate"
          }
        },
